Fresh Pi session: WRITE AN AGILE USE CASE, NOT AN IMPLEMENTATION DESIGN.

Inputs:
- User prompt: {{run.dir}}/prompt/prompt.md
- Repository root: {{inputs.repo-root}}
- Base branch: {{inputs.base-branch}}
- Revision issues, if any: {{run.issues-file}}

Goal:
Translate the request into one concise agile use case describing actor intent and externally observable behavior.

Rules:
- Inspect the repository only to understand existing behavior and vocabulary.
- Do not edit source code, tests, workflow definitions, or repository files.
- Do not prescribe files, classes, architecture, algorithms, or implementation steps.
- Include: title, primary actor, goal, trigger, preconditions, numbered main success scenario, alternate/exception flows, postconditions, scope boundaries, and explicit assumptions/open questions.
- Keep actor actions and system responses distinct.
- Include relevant behavior that must remain unchanged.
- Use the smallest coherent interpretation supported by the prompt and repository.
- Resolve revision issues when present. Fail only if a safe behavioral scope cannot be stated.

Write:
- Use case: {{run.dir}}/use-case/use-case-{{run.round}}.md
- Status: {{run.dir}}/use-case/status-{{run.round}}.json

Status examples:
{"status":"pass","summary":"use case ready for approval","issues_file":null}
{"status":"fail","summary":"use case needs revision","issues_file":null}
